title: CelebrateOne Areas
description: This layer includes eight priority areas for the CelebrateOne initiative?to reduce the community?s alarming infant mortality rate by 40 percent and cut the racial health disparity gap in half by 2020.?

title: Parking Inventory
description: This file geodatabase contains the following parking items: On-Street Meters (provided by City of Columbus), On-Street Non-Metered, a Traffic Analysis Zone Boundary (provided by MORPC), and Parking Facilities.

title: Parcels
description:
The Parcel Polygon layer contains polygons depicting the taxable areas of parcels for all of Summit County.To filter your search by Municipality select the table?tab and scroll the table to the right
until you reach the TaxDistrict column, click on TaxDistrict and
it will add a filter. To find out what Tax District Codes are for the municipality you want the Tax District Codes as listed here - http://fiscaloffice.summitoh.net/index.php/component/jdownloads/viewcategory/25. Select the latest year and open the PDF. *Note these are not alphabetical in order but numerical so check the entire PDF to get all Tax District Values for your municipality*
